<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875DB10719E0543DFB8EFC99" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB10719E0543DFB48FD85" blockId="18.[696,1292,559,986]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875DB10719E0543DFCC4FDAD" bold="true" box="[697,848,559,592]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071803543DFA96FDAD" authority="Baird, 1858" authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" box="[858,1282,559,592]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispidus">Perognathus hispidus Baird, 1858</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875DB10719E05449FB48FD85" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894336" box="[697,1244,603,632]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Charco Escondido, Tamaulipas, Mexico.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB10719E0546CFB8EFC99" blockId="18.[696,1292,559,986]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, C. 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071F5654B7FBECFD3B" authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" box="[1039,1144,677,710]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispidus">hispidus</taxonomicName>
is one of the three “ancient” clades of coarse-haired pocket mice. Three subspecies are recognized, following the 2012 revision by J. J. Andersen and J. E. Light.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875DB10719E05579FD04FB35" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" type="synonymic_list">
<caption id="E0EB6638875DB10719E05579FD04FB35" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6611224" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6611224" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6611224/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" targetBox="[83,673,571,985]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB10719E05579FBDEFC71" blockId="18.[696,1292,559,986]" box="[697,1098,875,908]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875DB10719E05579FBDEFC71" bold="true" box="[697,1098,875,908]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB10719E45580FEF4FBD6" blockId="18.[696,1292,559,986]" lastBlockId="18.[83,1294,994,2919]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB10719E45580FBB0FC4E" authority="Baird, 1858" authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[701,1060,914,947]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hispidus" subSpecies="hispidus">C.h.hispidusBaird,1858—SWUSA,NE&amp;NCMexico(GulfcoastofSTexas,NECoahuila,NENuevoLeon,Tamaulipas,andAltiplanoofECDurangoandNSanLuisPotositoHidalgo).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1071B03522BFC29FB84" blockId="18.[83,1294,994,2919]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071B03522BFE73FBAF" authority="J. A. Allen, 1894" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1894" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[90,487,1081,1106]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hispidus" subSpecies="conditi">C.h.conditiJ.A.Allen,1894—SWUSAandNMexico(C.h.DesertfromSEArizonaandSWNewMexico,CC.h.,toNCDurango).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1071B03526DFD04FB35" blockId="18.[83,1294,994,2919]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071B03526DFD96FB5D" authority="Merriam, 1889" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" box="[90,514,1151,1184]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hispidus" subSpecies="paradoxus">C. h. paradoxus Merriam, 1889</taxonomicName>
— WC USA (Great Plains of S North Dakota to E New Mexico, N &amp; C Texas, and W Louisiana).
</paragraph>
